{{Infobox scientist | name = Ahmet Şimşirgil | image = Ahmet şimşirgil.jpg | caption = Şimşirgil in May 2012 | birth_name = | birth_date = 25 May 1959 | death_date = | death_place = | birth_place = [[Boyabat]], [[Turkey]] | occupation = Historian, academic | religion = [[Sunni Islam]] | website = [http://ahmetsimsirgil.com/ Ahmet Şimşirgil] }}
'''Ahmet Şimşirgil''' (born 25 May 1959, in [[Sinop, Turkey|Sinop]]) is a Turkish academic. He is a [[professor]] of [[Ottoman history]] on the historical period which extends from the conquest of [[Istanbul]] in the Faculty of Science and Literature at the [[Marmara University]].<ref>http://www.sondakika.com/haber-tarihci-simsirgil-den-muhtesem-yuzyil-2480966/</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.beyazgazete.com/haber/2010/05/07/osmanli-devleti-nin-kurulusundaki-dinamikler-konferansi.html |title=Archived copy |access-date=2011-01-31 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110905120553/http://www.beyazgazete.com/haber/2010/05/07/osmanli-devleti-nin-kurulusundaki-dinamikler-konferansi.html |archive-date=2011-09-05 |dead-url=yes |df= }}</ref>
He has prepared and published the memories of [[Barbarossa Hayreddin Pasha]] as "''Kaptan Paşa'nın Seyir Defteri''" (''The Logbook of the Captain Pasha'') by [[Babıali Cultural Publications|Babıali Kültür Yayıncılığı]], a Turkish [[publishing house]] based in Istanbul.
