'''Arthur H. Cole''' (1889–1974) was an economic historian and was the head of the [[Harvard University Business School]]'s library.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.whav.net/cms/hall-of-fame-to-induct-harvards-cole-boston-athenaeum-founder-shaw/|title=Hall of Fame to Induct Harvard's Cole, Boston Athanaeum Founder Shaw|last=|first=|date=|website=|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|access-date=}}</ref> Cole created the Research Center in Entrepreneurial History that was addressed by Joseph Schumpeter, and that had as participants several graduate students who later went on to distinguished careers in economic history.<ref>{{Cite journal|last=Hughes|first=Johnathan|date=1983|title=Arthur Cole and Entrepreneurial History|url=|journal=Business and Economic History|volume=12|pages=133-144|via=}}</ref>
He graduated from [[Bowdoin College]] and [[Harvard University]].
