{{Infobox person | name = Yoav Gelber | birth_date = {{birth date and age|1943|9|25}} | birth_place = [[Mandatory Palestine|Mandate Palestine]] | death_date = | death_place = | education = [[Hebrew University]] | occupation = Historian }}
'''Yoav Gelber''' ({{lang-he|יואב גלבר}}; born September 25, 1943) is a professor of history at the [[University of Haifa]], and was formerly a visiting professor at The [[University of Texas]] at Austin.
He was born in [[Mandatory Palestine]] in 1943 and studied world and Jewish history at the [[Hebrew University]] of [[Jerusalem]] and is an expert on the history of the [[Israel Defense Forces]].<ref name="segev">[[Tom Segev]]: [http://www.ee.bgu.ac.il/~censor/katz-directory/02-05-23segev-haaretz-pappe-trial.pdf His colleagues call him a traitor] ([[Haaretz]], 23 May 2002).</ref> Yoav Gelber is also known to have been a vocal opponent of [[Ilan Pappé]] when the latter was employed by the University of Haifa.<ref name="segev" /><ref>Neri Livneh: [http://www.haaretz.com/hasen/pages/ShArt.jhtml?itemNo=76007 Post-Zionism only rings once] ([[Haaretz]], 20 September 2001).</ref>
In 1973 Gelber served as the academic and military assistant to the [[Agranat Commission]], and in 1982 participated in the official inquiry into the 1933 death of [[Haim Arlosoroff]].<ref>{{cite book|title=Palestine 1948: War, Escape and the Emergence of the Palestinian Refugee Problem|author=Gelber, Yoav|year=2001|edition=Second Edition (2006)|page=0 (back cover)|isbn=978-1-84519-075-0}}</ref>
